    "Background": {
      "text": "Pathologic state cccurs when internal or external hemorrhoid plexus become engorged, prolapsed, or thrombosed\nBleeding is usually limited (surface of stool, on toilet tissue, at end of defecation)\nPassage of blood clots requires evaluation for colon lesions",
      "subsections": {
        "Risk_Factors": {
          "text": "Constipation\nand straining at stool\nFrequent\ndiarrhea\nOlder age\nIBD",
